## Palm Beach, Florida

[Town](/Town_(Florida)) in [Palm Beach County, Florida](/Palm_Beach_County,_Florida), United States

Palm Beach, Florida. An incorporated town, if you can even call it that. It sits on a sliver of land, a [barrier island](/Barrier_island) precariously perched between the [Intracoastal Waterway](/Intracoastal_Waterway) and the vast, indifferent Atlantic. It’s part of the sprawling [South Florida metropolitan area](/South_Florida_metropolitan_area), though it prefers to think of itself as a world apart. As of the [2020 census](/2020_United_States_census), a mere 9,245 souls called this place home year-round. A blink-and-you'll-miss-it population, especially when you consider the transient influx during the "season."

